    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "No, <code>java.util.Date</code> is <i>not</i> deprecated, not as of Java 8. Some of its methods are deprecated but not the entire class. But you should avoid both <code>java.util.Date</code> and <code>java.util.Calendar</code> as they are notoriously troublesome, confusing, and flawed. Instead use either <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/package-summary.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">java.time</a> (in Java 8) or <a href=\"http://www.joda.org/joda-time/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Joda-Time</a>."
  } ],
