    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want the year of any date object, I used the following method:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int getYearFromDate(Date date) {\n    int result = -1;\n    if (date != null) {\n        Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();\n        cal.setTime(date);\n        result = cal.get(Calendar.YEAR);\n    }\n    return result;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5132802,
      "reputation" : 367,
      "user_id" : 4112413,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c0e136ddf812c2a631ae0389ffeddfc4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
